modules.description: Compares two values of type t using a lexicographical order defined by their structure. It operates on the abstract type t, which represents structured data elements. This function is used to determine ordering in sorted collections or during equality checks.

Provides priority queue operations such as insertion, extraction of the minimum element, and heapification. Works with arrays of ordered elements, supporting in-place modification and efficient access. Used to implement scheduling algorithms and graph traversal methods requiring ordered element retrieval.

Provides comparison functionality for heap elements, enabling ordered insertion and extraction. Operates on the `t` type, which represents individual heap nodes or values. Used to maintain priority order in real-time task scheduling and event-driven systems.
